Giuseppe Staffa (1807-1877) was an Italian composer and conductor. He is best remembered for his seven operas which he composed between 1827 and 1852. He was active as a conductor in Naples at the Teatro del Fondo and Teatro Nuovo.[1] One of his students was Enrico Bevignani. 
